# 🏠 RentifyX — Rental Marketplace Platform

**RentifyX** is a full-stack rental marketplace web application built with PHP, MySQL, Bootstrap 5, and Cloudinary. It connects vendors (item listers) with buyers (renters) through a dual-role system, supporting product listings, rental requests, buyer/vendor dashboards, and cloud-hosted product images.

> Built as a final-year project by [vighs08](https://github.com/vighs08).

---

## ✨ Features

### For Buyers (Users)
- Browse and search all rental listings with category filters
- View detailed product pages with up to 3 images
- Submit rental requests with delivery address and payment method
- Track pending and past rental requests from a personal dashboard
- Edit buyer profile (name, phone, preferred payment, delivery address)

### For Vendors
- Register as a vendor with store name and business address
- List items for rent with multiple image uploads (via Cloudinary)
- Edit and delete product listings
- Manage incoming buyer requests
- View buyer details and transaction history from the vendor dashboard
- Create product categories

### General
- Role-based access control (user / vendor)
- Secure login with bcrypt password hashing
- Session-based authentication with protected routes
- Responsive UI using Bootstrap 5
- Search bar and category-based filtering on product listings

---

## 📁 Project Structure

```
Rentyfx/
├── index.php                # Landing page
├── login.php                # User login
├── signup.php               # User registration (auto-login after signup)
├── navbar.php               # Shared top navbar (with search + role-based links)
├── authNav.php              # Auth-page sidebar nav
│
├── products_listing.php     # Main product grid with search & category filters
├── productsDetails.php      # Individual product detail page
│
├── buyerProfile.php         # Buyer dashboard (orders, pending requests, profile)
├── edit_data.php            # Edit buyer profile details
├── temp_request.php         # Submit a rental request for an item
│
├── vendorRegistration.php   # Register current user as a vendor
├── vendor_dashboard.php     # Vendor dashboard (listings, buyers, earnings)
├── userprofile.php          # Vendor profile view
├── editVenderInfo.php       # Edit vendor business info
│
├── addProducts.php          # Add new rental product (with Cloudinary upload)
├── editProduct.php          # Edit existing product
├── createCategory.php       # Create a new product category
│
├── buyers_section.php       # Partial: buyer table for vendor dashboard
├── db_connect.php           # MySQL database connection
├── config.php               # Cloudinary API credentials
│
├── composer.json            # PHP dependencies (Cloudinary SDK)
└── vendor/                  # Composer-managed packages
    ├── cloudinary/cloudinary_php
    ├── guzzlehttp/guzzle
    ├── monolog/monolog
    └── ...
```

---

## 🗄️ Database Schema

Database name: `rentfyx`

| Table                  | Key Columns                                                                 |
|------------------------|-----------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| `users`                | `userID`, `First_Name`, `Last_Name`, `email`, `password` (bcrypt), `phoneNumber`, `role` (`user`/`vendor`), `createdAt` |
| `vendors`              | `vendorID`, `userID` (FK), `storeName`, `businessAddress`, `rating`, `joinedAt` |
| `buyers`               | `buyerID`, `userID` (FK), `preferredPaymentMethod`, `deliveryAddress`       |
| `items`                | `itemID`, `vendorID` (FK), `categoryID` (FK), `title`, `description`, `price`, `status`, `createdAt` |
| `item_images`          | `itemID` (FK), `imageUrl`, `imageURL2`, `imageURL3`                        |
| `categories`           | `categoryID`, `categoryName`, `description`, `userID`, `createdAt`         |
| `temppurchaserequests` | `RequestID`, `UserID`, `VendorID`, `RentalItemID`, `Token`, `RequestDate`, `Status` |
| `transactions`         | `transactionDate`, `paymentStatus`, `deliveryStatus`, `totalAmount`, `buyerID`, `sellerID` |

