## 🛠️ Tech Stack

| Layer        | Technology                              |
|--------------|-----------------------------------------|
| Backend      | PHP 8.x                                 |
| Database     | MySQL (via `mysqli` with prepared stmts)|
| Frontend     | HTML5, CSS3, Bootstrap 5.3              |
| Image Hosting| Cloudinary PHP SDK v3                   |
| HTTP Client  | Guzzle (via Composer)                   |
| Logging      | Monolog (Cloudinary dependency)         |
| Dev Server   | XAMPP (Apache + MySQL)                  |

---

## ⚠️ Known Issues & Security Notes

This project was built as a final-year academic project. Before any production deployment, the following should be addressed:

- **🔐 Exposed Cloudinary credentials** — `config.php` has API keys committed directly to the repository. Rotate these immediately and use environment variables or a `.env` file.
- **🔐 Exposed DB credentials** — `db_connect.php` has hardcoded database credentials. Use environment variables instead.
- **🛡️ No CSRF protection** — Forms do not include CSRF tokens. Add them for all state-changing operations.
- **🛡️ Inconsistent input sanitization** — Some pages use `real_escape_string()` instead of prepared statements. Migrate all queries fully to prepared statements.
- **🛡️ No rate limiting** — Login has no brute-force protection.
- **📋 Debug output** — `addProducts.php` echoes a debug message to the browser. Remove before any public deployment.
- **📦 `vendor/` committed** — The Composer `vendor/` directory is tracked in git. Add it to `.gitignore` and let users run `composer install`.

